✅ Task Manager App
A full-stack task management application built with Next.js, Tailwind CSS, and a Node.js/Express backend with JWT authentication.

Features

🔐 Authentication — Register and login with JWT-based auth
✅ Task Management — Add, edit, delete, and toggle tasks
🔍 Search — Live search across your tasks
🗂️ Filter — Filter by All, Pending, or Done
📊 Progress Bar — Visual completion tracker
🌙 Dark / Light Mode — Toggle between themes
🔔 Toast Notifications — Feedback via react-hot-toast


Tech Stack
LayerTechnologyFrontendNext.js 14 (App Router), Tailwind CSSBackendNode.js, ExpressAuthJWT (Access Tokens)Notificationsreact-hot-toast

Getting Started
Prerequisites

Node.js 18+
npm or yarn

1. Clone the repository
bashgit clone https://github.com/your-username/task-manager.git
cd task-manager
2. Start the backend
bashcd server
npm install
npm run dev
# Runs on http://localhost:5000
3. Start the frontend
bashcd client
npm install
npm run dev
# Runs on http://localhost:3000

API Endpoints
MethodEndpointDescriptionPOST/auth/registerRegister a new userPOST/auth/loginLogin and receive access tokenGET/tasksGet all tasksPOST/tasksCreate a new taskPATCH/tasks/:idUpdate a task titlePATCH/tasks/:id/toggleToggle task completionDELETE/tasks/:idDelete a task

Project Structure
├── client/                 # Next.js frontend
│   └── app/
│       ├── login/          # Login page
│       ├── register/       # Register page
│       └── dashboard/      # Task dashboard
└── server/                 # Express backend
    └── routes/
        ├── auth.js         # Auth routes
        └── tasks.js        # Task routes

